Additional Disclaimer

TabScroll hooks into Windows mouse and keyboard input at the system level. This may conflict with anti-cheat software, security tools, or other input-monitoring applications.

The author is not responsible for any unintended behavior, system instability, software conflicts, account restrictions, or data loss arising from the use of this software. Use at your own risk.

You are solely responsible for ensuring that the use of TabScroll complies with the terms of any software, service, or game you use it with.

Privacy

TabScroll collects no personal data and makes no network requests.

The only data written locally is:

A configuration (.ini) file stored on your machine

An optional Windows registry entry if you enable "Start with Windows"

All data remains on your device.